TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lan, Chunhua
T1  - An Out-of-Sample Evaluation of Dynamic Portfolio Strategies*
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfu052
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 19
IS  - 6
SP  - 2359
EP  - 2399
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This article evaluates out-of-sample portfolio performance for a real-time investor who can exploit time variation in the conditional mean and volatility of stock returns in optimizing a multiperiod portfolio choice problem. With the presence of parameter uncertainty, our out-of-sample analysis shows that ignoring time variation in the first two return moments leads to significant utility costs of at least 1.97% of annualized certainty equivalent return. Accounting for the time-varying risk premium plays a more important role than considering time-varying volatility in improving portfolio performance. Interestingly, behaving myopically or ignoring the hedge against changes in future investment opportunities can lead to small out-of-sample utility losses or even utility gains.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfu052
ER  - 



